ce:section.ce:para:
In a typical experiment, 30–300 μL chloride solution of Fe3+ (0.03 mol/L), Cu2+ (3 mol/L), Cr3+ (3 mol/L), Sc3+ (1 mol/L), Al3+ (3 mol/L), Ga3+ (3 mol/L) was added into 3 mL of GQDs solution and the mixed solution was sonicated for 2 h, respectively. The fluorescence spectra of the mixed solution and pristine GQDs solution were detected by fluorescence spectrometer. The relative fluorescence ratio (F/F0
                        ) was used to evaluate the fluorescence quenching efficiency, where F0
                         and F represent the PL intensity of the GQDs solution before and after being added metal ions, respectively. The PL intensity of these solutions before and after being added salt solution was measured under UV irradiation (center wavelength 365 nm).
